These days, manycustomers choose to order products by mail or electronic order, orby phone to a toll-free number, he said.
Some of its products include diet aids, athleticperformance-boosters and many ``herbal ecstasy'' intoxicants thatteen-agers buy at convenience stores to get an amphetamine-like``buzz'' or ``high.''
``Somehow there is theidea that if you use a plant directly or extract a tea it will bemore effective and have less side effects (than approved drugs) andthat's not true.''
With millions of people taking ephedrine each year, Ellisargued, a few cases of adverse effects are to be expected.
